## Customer Work Tracking

**Target:** 30% of time on customer/business work (not building)

### Low-Bar Customer Actions (Remind User These Count)

Customer contact doesn't mean formal sales calls. It includes:

- ✅ Text GP with screenshot/question (30 seconds)
- ✅ Quick feedback survey (1 minute)  
- ✅ Casual coffee chat (30 minutes)
- ✅ Email update to GP list (1 hour, reaches many)
- ✅ LinkedIn posts via Ting (GPs commenting = contact)
- ✅ PHO outreach emails
- ✅ Demo prep or delivery
- ✅ Customer feedback review

**Goal:** Lower the barrier. Make it feel easy.

### Reminder Schedule

**Wednesday check** (if 0 customer contacts):
- Tone: Gentle and helpful
- "No customer work yet this week. Consider: [suggest specific low-bar action]"
- Example: "Could you text [GP name] about [feature]? Just a quick screenshot?"

**Friday check** (if 0 customer contacts):
- Tone: Firmer but supportive
- "Week ending with zero customer contact. Time allocation goal: 30% customer/business work."
- "Who could you reach out to before week ends? [suggest 2-3 specific people]"

**Never block work** - just remind and suggest.

